cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about cell event detection using deep learning methods, specifically convolutional long short-term memory (LSTM) models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the need for a large annotated training dataset, which suggests the possibility of using semi-supervised learning methods, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also proposes a novel method for optimal length detection, which involves unsupervised learning and inference, indicating the possibility of using artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on phase-contrast microscopy videos, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
